DOJ Employee Says Coworkers Discuss ìResistingî Trump from Within the DepartmentVideo footage of a Department of Justice employee discussing the ìresistî movement within the agency was captured by investigative journalism organization, Project Veritas, as part of an explosive series on the ìDeep State.îDOJ paralegal, Allison Hrabar, was asked by an undercover Project Veritas journalist whether or not her fellow DOJ employees were doing anything to ìfight against Trump.îìUm, yeah, I mean a lot of us talk about it, so most of them are like vaguely politically involved, so they might support candidates and do fundraisers, and some of them canvas,î she replied. ìAnd thereís a lot of talk about how we can like, resist from inside and thereís a lot of, kind of like, push back.î
